posts.message:
These instant apps, produced by an array of small startups and major companies including McDonalds and Apple-backed Didi Chuxing, bypass Apple’s App Store entirely. Accessible only within WeChat, they look and feel like apps, but they can be discarded as easily and quickly as a chat.

Facebook is behind another big threat to Apple: chatbots

posts.description: With its newest feature, WeChat wants you never to download or install another app.

posts.message: This seems to be an index based on the popularity of searches for programming language.  So the claim that _"The index can be used to check whether your programming skills are still up to date or to make a strategic decision about what programming language should be adopted when starting to build a new software system"_ seems to be questionable at the very least.
